description:
A deluxe, leather bound limited edition reprint collection of all of Frank Bellamy's comic strips from Swift, including King Arthur, Robin Hood, the Swiss Family Robinson and his contributions to other strips.

Includes a foreword by Dave Gibbons.

Deluxe, limited edition collection all of the Wulf the Briton strips illustrated (and mostly written) by Ron Embleton for Express Weekly. Also available as an even more limited edition leather-bound volume.

Note

While this volume includes all of Embleton's work on Wulf the Briton, which comprises almost all the Wulf the Briton stories, it does not include the stories drawn by other artists prior to Embleton starting on the series. The "complete" part of the title refers to Ron Embleton's work, not the character.

volume.name: Ron Embleton's Wulf the Briton The Complete Adventures

description: Book Palace Books limited edition collection reprinting Don Lawrence's Western strips Wells Fargo (from Zip in 1958 and Swift in 1959-1961) and Pony Express (from Swift, 1961-1963)
Ever since she got her powers, Sarah Mosley searches for her kid sister, Penny. But will she like what she finds?

A collection of the entire run of the classic British strip The Phantom Patrol, about a group of World War II Allied soldiers led by Sergeant Joe Trimm (and their German prisoner) who discover a crashed UFO on the island of Crete in 1941. Pinned down by the Nazis, they used a time travel device stolen from the alien spaceship to escape, but by doing so they become lost from time and, with no idea how to control what historical period the device will take them to, they find themselves jumping back and forth through history, facing dinosaurs, pirates, giant wasps, Vikings and Roman armies as they seek to find their way back to their own era.

Originally published in Swift, written by Willie Paterson and drawn by Ron Embleton, the collection features a new wraparound cover by Chris Weston.

Collection of all the Cursitor Doom strips from Smash! with a new wraparound cover by John Ridgway.

This collection features all the occult investigator's adventures with the exception of his appearances in the new bookend sections of Quality's Steel Claw reprint series, Doom's story in the 2000 AD Action Special, which has copyright issues due to being published and thus owned by Fleetway Editions, who didn't actually own the character himself, and Doom's appearances in Wildstorm's Albion as part of an ensemble cast of IPC characters.

Collection of classic comic strips and art by Cecil Langley Doughty. The four strips are from Look and Learn:

  • Pott's Progress
  • The Crusader
  • A Sword for the Stadtholder
  • The Black Pirate.

First volume of Mike Butterworth and Bill Lacey's World War I aerial warfare epic Eagles of the Western Front, originally published in Look and Learn. Pilot Harry Hawkes joins the newly formed Royal Flying Corps and finds himself up against the first German flying ace, Max Immelmann, the "Eagle of Lille."

Second volume of Mike Butterworth and Bill Lacey's World War I aerial warfare epic Eagles of the Western Front from Look and Learn. It is 1916, and RFC pilot Harry Hawkes faces the lethal German flying aces Oswald Boelke and the Red Baron himself, Manfred von Richthofen!

Third and final volume of Mike Butterworth and Bill Lacey's World War I aerial warfare epic Eagles of the Western Front from Look and Learn. Completing the collection, in this volume it is 1917, and RFC pilot Harry Hawkes has his final showdown with the Red Baron and his Flying Circus.
The first issue of Eagle to feature Frank Bellamy and Tom Tully's Heros the Spartan.

Contents include:

description: The Little Green Men return! Three alien misfits on a mission to conquer Earth discover the hard way that humanity isn't all that humane. Arriving on our globe of green and blue only to learn that they're a mere three inches tall, the trio of interplanetary outcasts prove that size really doesn't matter after all, as they try to conquer the Earth a little bit at a time!

description: THE DARK CHAMBER' Part One It is the dawn of World War I, and Sherlock Holmes has been dead for 20 years. Holmes' enemy - Professor James Moriarty - is a lost man. MI5 blackmails Moriarty into finding Holmes' long-lost brother, Mycroft, but what at first appears to be a routine case leads to a web of intrigue that involves a psychic box and its creator, a woman from Moriarty's past, and a new villain that threatens to be greater than Moriarty ever was!
name: Volume 1

description: In the wake of THE DARK CHAMBER, Professor Moriarty finds himself afflicted with unsettling visions. He sets sail for Burma in search of an old ally, but finds himself caught up in a city on the brink of revolt, a troublesome Imperial Policeman, and a secret that holds the key to his destiny.
name: Volume 2

description: A bold new chapter in SPAWN begins here! Jim Downing is the new Spawn, but he's also an internationally known faith healer and media darling. How long can these dual lives continue before the world finds out the truth? And watch out for the Clown and his alliance with Bludd, the vampire master - they have plans of their own for Jim as well... Collects SPAWN #201-206.
name: Volume 1

description: Jim Downing's re-birth as the newest Hellspawn continues! No one is safe from the 'Curse of the Spawn,' as the darkness surrounding Jim's life beings to spread, pulling Twitch and Detective Rowand deeper into a shadowy world of intrigue and horror. A crash course on the origins of Jim's new powers and the man known as Al Simmons leads to a violent confrontation with the one person Jim thought he could trust... Clown. Collects SPAWN #207-212.
name: Volume 2

description: Collects : X-Factor (2006) #213-219

The 17th volume of the comprehensive and multiple award-winning Complete Crumb Comics series — nominated for both 2003 Harvey and Eisner Awards — completes the 1980s and leads into the 1990s. This was a creatively fertile period for Crumb, who had given up the editorial reins of his own legendary Weirdo magazine, allowing him to get back to the proverbial drawing board. Included are Crumb's contributions to Weirdo from this period, as well as work from Whole Earth Review, Zap Comix, Premiere magazine, as well as many other rare gems. Featured are classics including "Cave Wimp" — the story of the first nerd — and "A Short History of America," amongst other Crumb classics. This volume, as with all volumes, includes a new introduction by Crumb as well as a new cover. TheComplete Crumb series leaves no stone unturned, publishing everything from Crumb's most well-known comics to little-seen commercial art and rarely-if-ever seen treasures from private collections and the artist's archives.
name: Cave Wimp

description: Torrebianca is a village in the lower reaches of Parma county, on the banks of the River Po. As he tries to find out how much truth there may be in an old legend, Harlan discovers that the inhabitants of Torrebianca are obsessed by the danger of the river, which centuries ago flooded and wrecked the entire old settlement. Ever since then, as soon as the first mists arrive in the fall, wistful songs of bygone days come wafting over from the opposite bank and, at night, some see the ghostly houses of the vanished township, appearing like a mirage. Even worse: for decades, in that isolated stretch of the county, people have mysteriously gone missing. Vladimiro the Lunatic saw a person being dragged into the river by the children of the drowned, the “Returnees”…
name: Il grande fiume

description: Arturo Solanas is obsessed by ghosts. They’re the specters of his victims. But he too is a victim: the soldiers who over twenty years ago organized the coup d’état in Argentina deprived him of his humanity, transforming him into a murderous vampire. The fact is, you see, that concealed among those instigators of the putsch there was notorious Condor, the Master of the Night who was allied with Ixtlàn, and also with Lord Marsden, the aristocrat Dampyr is trying to chase down. At first the search takes Harlan Draka to Madrid, where Solanas is killing his enemies one by one. He and Dampyr have some adversaries in common… but a Dampyr’s task is to kill and eliminate vampires…
name: Danza con la morte

description: Humpty Dumpty, Goosey Gander, Dama Trot… Why have the innocent and fanciful characters of nursery rhymes, the children's tales of the English tradition, turned into murderous monsters on the streets of London? Detective Simon Fane, of Scotland Yard, an expert in unusual cases, is put on the case. And suspect number one is the notorious braggart vampire-killer Dean Barrymore, president of the Club of Occult Presences. Dean, together with his colleague Jack Tarrant and the archeologist Matthew Shady, is trying to locate the hideout of Lord Marsden, the London Vampire. When Harlan, Tesla and Kurjak are called to take part in the investigation as well, the vampiresque investigation proceeds by leaps and bounds. Shame, though, that Fane is so interfering… But what do nursery rhymes have to do with a Master of the Night? And why has Fane forgotten about his unhappy childhood at the Morningstar orphanage? What lies concealed in the underground cellars of the Temsek company, in the Thames docklands? And which of little orphan kid Tiny's dreams can open the door to the mysterious house in the forest, where Dama Trot lives?…
name: Gli Orrori di Londra

description:
Il Signore delle Vespe

A horrible legend about the “Thousand-spiked Demon from Hell” becomes true in Brighton, England, where the ghost hunter, Maud Nightingale, with his friend Utterson bought the wrong thing at an auction of old artifacts. Caught in the middle between killer wasps and ruthless Chinese gangsters, their only hope is the Dampyr’s help...

Il segreto del bosco

Who doesn’t know Bomarzo’s “magic wood”? But what’s its real secret? Two self-appointed American alchemists try to find out, performing human sacrifices in the park created by Vicino Orsini. But they make a mistake when they use the Dampyr’s blood...

Ombre nella giungla

Undeads have been seen in the forest of Pantanal, and they appearingly formed a pack without a Master... Harlan and his friends descend the river, to face one of their most dangerous adventures …
name: Il signore delle vespe

description:
Spectriana

An infernal book, emerged from the Theater Library, cause in the people who leaf through it incredible hallucinations and dangerous experiences, when the tales in its pages come to life. Harlan faces a shapeless monster and a living island; Kurjak has to tangle with a hallucinating celebration and an unpredictable tattoo master; Tesla becomes a child again and is tempted by a young Samael, while Caleb Lost is at risk of falling in love with a beautiful she-devil.

Gargoyle

A heart of stone that’s been beating for revenge for a century. A family oppressed by a bloody curse, and a magical castle in the heart of Bavaria…
name: Spectriana - Gargoyle

description:
Magia africana

In the middle of the bloody clash of two African warlords, Lisimba and Mabasi, there’s a mystic variation: the “black ‘mbandwa”, the black magic able to animate killer amulets using the power of the mind. called by Arno from the “Medical Team”, Harlan and co. will find themselves caught in the crossfire...

La notte della taranta

Under the Salento sun, musicologist Giordano heals the neurosis of his female patients with a therapy based on the obsessive rhytm of the “taranta” music. A dead body in the fields, covered by tarantulas, brings back to light a mystery buried in the past, its solution hidden in an old unhallowed church...

Marea rossa

In the Philippine Sea, the mad scientist Diunerjuf, lord of the zombies, revives the dead with a scientific concoction based on the venom of the fugu, the globefish. Dampyr will seek to ally with other scientists to find a remedy for the army of the living dead...
name: Magia africana

NEW THRILL! From the breathtaking imaginations of Al Ewing and Brendan McCarthy comes the realm of Zilk – a province on the fringes of the imagination. Ruled over by the Zultan, figurehead of the Zilk dynasty, it’s a world where science and magic meet – and none is more powerful, or more famous, than the Zaucer himself. Vain, arrogant and accustomed to his celebrity status, he’s the wizard of the royal court – and many would like to see him removed permanently…!
